        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          The first Anderlecht goal was miles offside and I can't for the life of me see what the linesman saw to rule it onside. That being said, we were still 2 goals up and should've closed the game out. A Mourinho-led team would've finished that game, closed down the midfield and defended tightly so Anderlecht didn't get a sniff. We, however, kept it open & attacking and couldn't close down the midfield because we don't have a top notch defensive midfielder. After Monreal gave away the penalty, I think the majority of Arsenal fans could see an equaliser coming. On the plus side, we should still go through albeit 2nd; Sanchez, Chamberlain and Welbeck were good & (most importantly) my 3-0 prediction was right. Even if it's for only 15 minutes, I'll take it!
